<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10034a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10034a">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10034a"> 34(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> I wish I had a yoke <font face="wake">D</font> / &mdash; a bit in my mouth</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La mani&egrave;re d&apos;atteler les animaux, chez les peuples anciens, &eacute;tait tout &agrave; fait diff&eacute;rente de la n&ocirc;tre. Les chevaux et mulets n&apos;avaient point d&apos;autre harnachement que des jougs de formes vari&eacute;es et quelquefois enjoliv&eacute;s de sculptures, qui leur retombaient sur le cou, dans une cavit&eacute; m&eacute;nag&eacute;e &agrave; cet effet. <font color="green">[Among the ancients, the manner of harnessing animals was altogether different from our own. Horses and mules had no harness other than a yoke, which came in various forms and was sometimes embellished with sculptures. This was sunk back into the neck, into a special cavity.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) ?34</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01013f" href="c01all.htm#c01013f">VI.C.01:013(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
